channel.title: HELP DAMAGED CACHE [metal fences, gates, varrock bank]
channel.description:
Hello evryone, recently I viewed aeolian's guide to fixing damaged cache, floating helmets instead of fences. But now I have "ice" instead of metal fences, gates etc. He had a guide for that too, but it didn't work, it only fixed my varrock fountain which had the same ice models. I'd like some help, there are pictures below, if anoyone could help i'd be very grateful, thanks.
Pictures
[IMG]http://i922.photobucket.com/albums/ad61/Luke_ya_digg/1.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i922.photobucket.com/albums/ad61/Luke_ya_digg/2.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i922.photobucket.com/albums/ad61/Luke_ya_digg/3.jpg[/img]

item.description:

[quote=“Fox0wnage, post:6, topic:286330”][quote author=ModAssassin link=topic=378678.msg2848438#msg2848438 date=1246403994]

Good idea, I should’ve thought of that, it would work if I replaced the models from another client correct?

no, the cache will just over ride you’re class8.java for some reason, just make a ‘back up’ [copy] of class8.java, delete the original, than replace the caches. than put the class.java back into the client, compile, and it should work 100%. have any problembs, just post
[/quote]

so this should fix it?[/quote]

yupp
